name: Lori and George Schappell
summary: Lori and George Schappell, the world's oldest conjoined twins, have passed away at the age of 62. The twins, who had been joined at the chest and abdomen since birth, held the Guinness World Record for being the oldest surviving conjoined twins. Lori and George had a unique bond and had lived a full and active life together, including traveling, writing a book, and appearing on television. Their passing is a sad loss for the medical community and for the world at large. They will be remembered as an inspiration to those who face challenges and as a symbol of the strength of the human spirit.
